The paper deals with the problem of autonomous acquisition of manipulation skills by a robot, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves the use of active learning and creativity, which are key areas of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of environment models, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
